{{Infobox government agency | agency_name = Department of Archaeology | nativename = पुरातत्व विभाग | seal = | seal_width = | seal_caption = | logo = | logo_width = | logo_caption = | formed = {{Start date|1998|12|31}} | preceding1 = Department of Civil Aviation | preceding2 = <!-- up to |preceding6= --> | dissolved = | superseding1 = | superseding2 = <!-- up to |superseding6= --> | agency_type = | jurisdiction = {{flag|Nepal|2015}} | headquarters = Ramshahpath, [[Kathmandu]], Nepal | coordinates = | motto = | employees = | budget = | minister1_name = Jitendra Narayan Dev | minister1_pfo = Minister of Culture, Tourism and Civil Aviation | minister2_name = | minister2_pfo = | deputyminister1_name = | deputyminister1_pfo = | deputyminister2_name = | deputyminister2_pfo = | deputyminister3_name = | deputyminister3_pfo = <!-- up to |deputyminister7_name= --> | chief1_name = Bhesh Narayan Dahal | chief1_position = Director General | chief2_name = | chief2_position = | public_protector = | deputy = | parent_department = | parent_agency = [[Ministry of Culture, Tourism and Civil Aviation (Nepal)|Ministry of Culture, Tourism and Civil Aviation]], [[Government of Nepal]] | child1_agency = | child2_agency = <!-- up to |child25_agency= --> | keydocument1 = <!-- up to |keydocument6= --> | website = http://www.doa.gov.np | map = | map_width = | map_caption = | footnotes = | embed = }}
The '''Department of Archaeology''' or DOA (estd 1953) is the primary organization for the archaeological research and protection of the cultural heritage under the government of [[Nepal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ekantipur.com/the-kathmandu-post/2012/08/09/metro/heritage-watch-archaeology-dept-archiving-pearls-of-great-price/238206.html |title=HERITAGE WATCH: Archaeology Dept archiving pearls of great price &#124; Metro &#124; :: The Kathmandu Post :: |publisher=Ekantipur.com |date= |accessdate=2015-07-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://m.ekantipur.com/2011/05/06/top-story/in-search-of-buddhas-maternal-home/333606.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-11-21 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20131121195401/http://m.ekantipur.com/2011/05/06/top-story/in-search-of-buddhas-maternal-home/333606.html |archivedate=2013-11-21 |df= }} </ref> After the [[April 2015 Nepal earthquake]] and [[May 2015 Nepal earthquake]], the Department got involved with analyzing and reconstructing the destruction of ancient buildings in Kathmandu.
