==List of jukebox musical films== *''[[Yankee Doodle Dandy]]'' (1942), a picture dealing with the life of Playwright and Composer [[George M. Cohan]], and featuring many of his greatest songs, which were among the most popular songs of their day (Late 19th Century-Early 20th Century). *''[[Meet Me in St. Louis]]'' (1945), featuring mostly popular songs from the earlier 20th century and three new songs written for Judy Garland. *''[[Till the Clouds Roll By]]'' (1946), a biopic of composer [[Jerome Kern]], featuring his songs. *''[[Easter Parade (film)|Easter Parade]]'' (1948), featuring a collection of songs by [[Irving Berlin]]. *''[[One Sunday Afternoon (1948 film)|One Sunday Afternoon]]'' (1948), featuring popular songs from the earlier 20th century. *''[[An American in Paris (film)|An American in Paris]]'' (1951), a fictionalized story based around [[George Gershwin]]'s "[[An American in Paris]]" suite. The score consists entirely of George and [[Ira Gershwin]] pieces, with "American in Paris" being a recurring theme. *''[[Singin' in the Rain]]'' (1952), featuring popular songs from the 1920s and '30s and songs by [[Arthur Freed]], with the exception of two numbers ("[[Make 'Em Laugh]]" and "Moses Supposes") *''[[Love Me or Leave Me (film)|Love Me or Leave Me]]'' (1955), featuring popular songs from the 1930s. *''[[Rock Around the Clock (film)|Rock Around the Clock]]'' (1956), the first rock-and-roll movie musical, featuring the commercial recordings of [[Bill Haley and His Comets]] and [[The Platters]]. *''Don't Knock the Rock'' (1957), another Bill Haley jukebox musical, with the commercial recordings of Haley, [[Little Richard]], and [[The Treniers]]. *''[[Hootenanny Hoot]]'' (1963), a low-budget MGM picture intended to capitalize on the Folk Music craze then sweeping America, featuring on-screen performances by [[Johnny Cash]], [[Judy Henske]], and several other Folk Music artists. *''[[Your Cheatin' Heart (film)|Your Cheatin' Heart]]'' (1964), based on the Life Story of [[Hank Williams]], and featuring many of his greatest songs. *''[[A Hard Day's Night (film)|A Hard Day's Night]]'' (1964), based on mostly previously unreleased songs of [[The Beatles]]. *''[[Help! (film)|Help!]]'' (1965), based on mostly previously unreleased songs of [[The Beatles]]. *''[[Yellow Submarine (1968 film)|Yellow Submarine]]'' (1968), based on the songs of [[The Beatles]]. *''[[At Long Last Love]]'' (1975), based on the songs of [[Cole Porter]]. *''[[All This and World War II]]'' (1976), a [[World War II]] documentary featuring the songs of [[The Beatles]]. *''[[New York, New York (1977 film)|New York, New York]]'' (1977), featuring popular music from the 1920s through the 1940s. *''[[Sgt. Pepper's Lonely Hearts Club Band (film)|Sgt. Pepper's Lonely Hearts Club Band]]'' (1978), based on the songs of [[The Beatles]] and their [[Sgt. Pepper's Lonely Hearts Club Band|album of the same name]]. *''[[All That Jazz (film)|All That Jazz]]'' (1979), featuring popular music from the earlier 20th century. *''[[Can't Stop the Music]]'' (1980), featuring contemporary [[disco music|disco]] songs. *''[[The Blues Brothers (film)|The Blues Brothers]]'' (1980), featuring various popular rhythm & blues songs. *''[[American Pop]]'' (1981), featuring rock songs from the 1960s and '70s. *''[[Purple Rain (film)|Purple Rain]]'' (1984), featuring previously unreleased music from [[Prince (musician)|Prince]] and [[The Original 7ven|The Time]]. *''[[Everyone Says I Love You]]'' (1996), featuring popular music from the earlier 20th century. *''[[Spice World (film)|Spice World]]'' (1997), based on the music of [[The Spice Girls]] *''[[Blues Brothers 2000]]'' (1998), featuring various popular rhythm & blues songs. *''[[Love's Labour's Lost (2000 film)|Love's Labour's Lost]]'' (2000), featuring classic Broadway songs of the 1930s. *''[[Moulin Rouge!]]'' (2001), featuring a variety of pop songs from various decades. *''[[Ray (film)|Ray]]'' (2004), based on the music of [[Ray Charles]] *''[[20 centímetros]]'' (2005), Various Artists, featuring a variety of pop songs from various decades. *''[[Walk the Line]]'' (2005), based on the music of [[Johnny Cash]]. *''[[Happy Feet]]'' (2006), featuring a variety of pop songs from various decades. *''[[Idlewild (film)|Idlewild]]'' (2006), featuring the songs of [[OutKast]] *''[[Romance & Cigarettes]]'' (2006), featuring mostly love themed pop-songs from the 1950s through '70s. *''[[Across the Universe (film)|Across the Universe]]'' (2007), featuring the songs of [[The Beatles]]. *''[[Stilyagi (film)|Stilyagi]]'' (2008), featuring Soviet rock songs from the 1970s and '80s. *''[[Mamma Mia! (film)|Mamma Mia!]]'' (2008), based on the musical ''[[Mamma Mia!]]'', which is based on the songs of [[ABBA]] * ''[[Gnomeo & Juliet]]'' (2011), based mostly on the music of [[Elton John]]. * ''[[Happy Feet Two]]'' (2011), featuring a variety of pop songs from various decades. * ''{{ill|Toi, moi, les autres|fr|Toi, moi, les autres}}'' (2011), featuring a variety of French songs. *''[[Pitch Perfect]]'' (2012), featuring songs of various genres and various artists. * ''[[Rock of Ages (2012 film)|Rock of Ages]]'' (2012), featuring hard rock and metal songs of the 1980s. *''[[Lovestruck: The Musical]]'' (2013), featuring various pop and dance songs of the 1980s through present. *''[[Sunshine on Leith (film)|Sunshine on Leith]]'' (2013), based on the Musical ''[[Sunshine on Leith (musical)|Sunshine on Leith]]'', which is based on the songs of [[The Proclaimers]] *''[[Jersey Boys (film)|Jersey Boys]]'' (2014), based on the musical ''[[Jersey Boys]]'', which is based on the music of [[The Four Seasons (band)|The Four Seasons]] *''[[Walking on Sunshine (film)|Walking on Sunshine]]'' (2014), featuring pop-songs from the 1980s. *''[[Pitch Perfect 2]]'' (2015), featuring songs of various genres and various artists. *''[[Strange Magic (film)|Strange Magic]]'' (2015) featuring various genres and various artists. *''[[Trolls (film)|Trolls]]'' (2016) featuring various genres and various artists. *''[[Sing (2016 American film)|Sing]]'' (2016) featuring various genres and various artists. *''[[Pitch Perfect 3]]'' (2017), featuring songs of various genres and various artists. *''[[Mamma Mia! Here We Go Again]]'' (2018), sequel to the [[Mamma Mia! (film)|first film]] based on the musical ''[[Mamma Mia!]]'', which is based on the songs of [[ABBA]].
==List of jukebox musical TV shows== *''[[Kids Incorporated]]'' (1984) *''[[Blackpool (TV serial)|Blackpool]]'' (2007) *''[[Viva Laughlin]]'' (2007) *''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]'' (2009) *''[[The Kitchen Musical]]'' (2011) *''[[Smash (U.S. TV series)|Smash]]'' (2012) *''[[Beat Bugs]]'' (2016), which uses a different [[Beatles]] song as the inspiration for each episode
